source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000010_ALISAIE<tab>Ah, there you are. You're just in time to welcome our guest...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000010_ALISAIE<tab>Tu ne pouvais pas mieux tomber<var 1D /var>! Nous étions justement en train d'accueillir... <var 1A 02 /var>un invité<var 1A 01 /var>.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000020_EMETSELCH<tab>Please. Did I not explicitly tell you that we would be meeting again soon?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000020_EMETSELCH<tab>Haaa... Toi aussi, tu tires cette tête<var 1D /var>? Je vous avais pourtant bien dit que nous nous reverrions bientôt<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000030_EMETSELCH<tab>Lest you forget, I made you a promise. I have no intention of meddling with your mission. I come only to observe.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000030_EMETSELCH<tab>Détendez-vous... Je ne suis pas là pour vous mettre des bâtons dans les roues. Je vous l'ai promis... Ce n'est qu'une petite visite de courtoisie.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000040_EMETSELCH<tab>Your Exarch friend in particular has piqued my curiosity. Summoning you all like that. Most impressive.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000040_EMETSELCH<tab>Je ne peux nier la curiosité que m'inspire ce très cher exarque, lui qui a fait venir en ce monde les héros d'un autre.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000050_THANCRED<tab>You honestly expect us to believe you've come only to observe? Or that you might deign to lift a finger to aid our cause if called upon?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000050_THANCRED<tab>Tu évoquais la possibilité d'une entente, de porter un regard nouveau les uns sur les autres...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000060_THANCRED<tab>Even if there were a sliver of truth in your words, I would never accept your help. Not in my darkest hour─not after all the suffering your kind has wrought.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000060_THANCRED<tab>Mais compte tenu de l'attitude des Asciens jusqu'à maintenant, je nous vois mal nous associer à l'un de vous.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000070_EMETSELCH<tab>So petty. I meant what I said and I said what I meant.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000070_EMETSELCH<tab>Du calme, pas besoin de prendre ce ton. Pourquoi ne pas tenter l'expérience avant de juger du résultat<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000080_EMETSELCH<tab>Wage your war against the sin eaters. Put each and every Lightwarden to the sword.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000080_EMETSELCH<tab>Pendant ce temps, vous n'avez qu'à continuer la chasse aux grands purgateurs...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000090_EMETSELCH<tab>Prove yourselves heroes brave and true, and I will be glad to embrace you as allies.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000090_EMETSELCH<tab>Quand vous en aurez fini, on verra si je vous trouve un quelconque intérêt. Alors seulement, je viendrai vous tendre une main secourable.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000100_EMETSELCH<tab>Allies worthy of bearing the burden of truth.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000100_EMETSELCH<tab>Je ne le ferai que si je discerne en vous des partenaires avec qui vivre et porter le fardeau de la vérité.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000110_EMETSELCH<tab>Surely such a partnership would be preferable to yet another round of fisticuffs?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000110_EMETSELCH<tab>Si cela vous déplaît, rien ne vous oblige à accepter mon offre. Nous reprendrons alors notre combat à mort. C'est simple comme bonjour, non<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000120_EMETSELCH<tab>...And thus did the olive branch wither and die. Pity.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000120_EMETSELCH<tab>Oooh... J'ai l'impression que vous ne me faites pas du tout confiance. Mes actes d'hier troublent votre jugement aujourd'hui...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000130_EMETSELCH<tab>Well─let no man say I did not try, futile as it was.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000130_EMETSELCH<tab>Bref<var 1D /var>! Inutile de perdre plus de temps en palabres. Retenez juste une chose...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000140_EMETSELCH<tab>Though I suspect you will seek me out when you grow tired of making the same mistakes.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000140_EMETSELCH<tab>Si vous êtes enclins à me prêter une oreille attentive, je vous dirai toute la vérité.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000150_EMETSELCH<tab>Difficult decisions lie ahead of you. Decisions best made with the benefit of knowledge to which only the eternal are privy.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000150_EMETSELCH<tab>Je vous dévoilerai le savoir que seuls des êtres comme nous, ancestraux et immortels, ont pu acquérir. Et vous devrez ensuite faire un choix.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000160_EMETSELCH<tab>For now, I shall resume my shadowy vigil. Whatever you choose to do, make sure it's worth watching, would you.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000160_EMETSELCH<tab>Allez, bon courage. Et par pitié, ne me faites pas mourir d'ennui. N'oubliez pas que je vous observe...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000170_ALISAIE<tab>What was that all about?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000170_ALISAIE<tab>Mais il se prend pour qui, lui<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000180_THANCRED<tab>A vain attempt to make us doubt our chosen course, most like. As if we'd believe a word that passed his lips.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000180_THANCRED<tab>Sa rhétorique est digne de son rôle d'empereur fondateur de Garlemald. Toutefois, ce n'est pas une raison pour croire un traître mot de son discours...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000190_THANCRED<tab>Unless you think there is some truth in what he says?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000190_THANCRED<tab>Et vous, qu'en pensez-vous<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_Q1_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>What will you say?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_Q1_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Que répondez-vous<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A1_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>A kernel, perhaps...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A1_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Laissons-lui le bénéfice du doute.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A1_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Not one jot.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A1_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Il est louche, c'est indéniable.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A1_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>I don't know. But if he crosses us, I'll make him wish he hadn't.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A1_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>Nous n'aurons qu'à nous débarrasser de lui s'il nous trahit.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000200_ALPHINAUD<tab>If he simply meant to lead us astray, he could have done so without revealing himself. At least, not in the manner he did.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000200_ALPHINAUD<tab>Tout à fait. Si son but était de nous duper, il ne se serait pas donné la peine de venir nous voir.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000210_ALPHINAUD<tab>I share your suspicion, of course. But if he simply meant to lead us astray, he could have done so without revealing himself. At least, not in the manner he did.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000210_ALPHINAUD<tab>Il est certes très étrange, mais si son but était de nous duper, il ne se serait pas donné la peine de venir jusqu'ici.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000220_ALPHINAUD<tab>I am sure you will. But consider for a moment: if he meant simply to lead us astray, he could have done so without revealing himself. At least, not in the manner he did.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000220_ALPHINAUD<tab>Votre assurance fait plaisir à entendre. Mais s'il cherchait à nous duper, il ne serait sans doute pas venu à notre rencontre.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000230_ALPHINAUD<tab>It goes without saying that an alliance with the Ascians is out of the question. But since we have no way of knowing where they might be hiding, it seems only logical to press on with our mission─even if our enemy seems content for it to succeed.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000230_ALPHINAUD<tab>Je n'irai pas jusqu'à dire qu'on devrait lui faire confiance, mais la vérité, c'est qu'on ne contrôlera jamais les Asciens. Alors autant nous concentrer sur notre but, tout en restant vigilants.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000240_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Then let us discuss the sin eaters.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000240_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Reprenons, alors... Laissez-moi vous parler de notre prochain objectif.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000250_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>I would begin by thanking you all for your efforts thus far.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000250_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Votre in<var 16 /var>ter<var 16 /var>ven<var 16 /var>tion a permis de venir à bout du grand purgateur d'Il Mheg.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000260_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>In striking down the Lightwardens of Lakeland and Il Mheg, you have accomplished more in your short time here than all of our forces managed in the last century.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000260_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Ça fait deux avec celui de Grand-Lac, et c'est notre plus belle avancée depuis le déluge de Lumière. Je ne vous remercierai jamais assez.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000270_THANCRED<tab>That may be, but the Wardens of Kholusia, Amh Araeng, and Rak'tika remain.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000270_THANCRED<tab>Si j'ai tout compris, les alentours de Kholusia, l'Amh Araeng et Rak'tika sont les dernières régions qui baignent encore dans la Lumière.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000280_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Indeed. And their precise whereabouts are as yet unknown.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000280_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Exactement... Et aucun grand purgateur n'y a encore été localisé.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000290_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Which is why I propose we divide our forces and conduct a systematic survey of each region. Once we have found our quarry, we may then determine how best to proceed.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000290_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Voilà pourquoi j'aimerais que nous nous répartissions le travail cette fois-ci. Qu'en dites-vous<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000300_ALISAIE<tab>I'll take Amh Araeng, in that case. I know the lie of the land well enough.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000300_ALISAIE<tab>Si personne n'a d'objection, je m'occupe de l'Amh Araeng. J'ai eu l'occasion de me fa<var 16 /var>mi<var 16 /var>lia<var 16 /var>ri<var 16 /var>ser un peu avec les lieux.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000310_ALPHINAUD<tab>If there are no objections, I will make for Kholusia. I have connections there both in and around Eulmore that may prove useful.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000310_ALPHINAUD<tab>Je prends Kholusia, dans ce cas. Je ne pourrai pas entrer dans Eulmore, mais quelques con<var 16 /var>nais<var 16 /var>san<var 16 /var>ces devraient pouvoir m'aider à l'extérieur de la cité.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000320_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Then I would ask that you journey to Rak'tika.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000320_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Vous autres, vous n'aurez qu'à aller à Rak'tika.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000330_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>There you will find Y'shtola. With her assistance, I doubt the Warden will evade your grasp for long.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000330_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Y'shtola s'y trouve déjà. Un petit coup de main ne sera sans doute pas de refus pour repérer le grand purgateur et lui régler son compte.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000340_RYNE<tab>Is Y'shtola the conjurer you and Urianger used to talk about?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000340_RYNE<tab>Y'shtola, c'est ce mage dont tu parlais avec Urianger<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000350_THANCRED<tab>That's right. Though we haven't spoken much since she left for the forest.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000350_THANCRED<tab>Oui, mais comme les autres, je n'ai plus tellement de nouvelles depuis qu'elle s'est installée là-bas.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000360_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>I fear I may be to blame for that. I had every intention of relaying the news of your arrival, but she is...disinclined to speak with me.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000360_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Elle ne me fait pas vraiment confiance... Je n'ai même pas pu la contacter pour la prévenir de notre ras<var 16 /var>sem<var 16 /var>ble<var 16 /var>ment.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000370_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>You have visited her, have you not? Might I trouble you to...?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000370_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Urianger, tu lui as plusieurs fois rendu visite, non<var 1D /var>? Puis-je te demander de les escorter<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000380_URIANGER<tab>'Twould be no trouble.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000380_URIANGER<tab>Entendu. Ils auraient bien du mal à entrer dans cette forêt sans mon aide de toute façon. Elle est aussi sombre qu'impénétrable.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000390_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>My thanks. While you are all out in the field, I shall be here attending to business. I had somewhat fancifully contemplated joining the search myself, but other matters demand my attention.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000390_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Merci. Je profiterai de votre absence pour accomplir une tâche en particulier...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000400_ALISAIE<tab>What's that?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000400_ALISAIE<tab>Qu'est-ce que c'est<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000410_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>A missive from Lord Vauthry. He invites me to join him in Eulmore to discuss the recent conflict at Lydha Lran.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000410_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Un pli de Vauthry. Il requiert ma présence à Eulmore pour discuter de notre conflit, me dit-il.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000420_ALISAIE<tab>And? Did he even bother to offer any bait? It's obviously a trap.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000420_ALISAIE<tab>Vous avez perdu la raison<var 1D /var>? C'est beaucoup trop risqué<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000430_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>I should be surprised if it were not. Nevertheless, I must seize this opportunity to speak with him, even if only a few words are exchanged.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000430_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Nous lui avons tenu tête sans fléchir. S'il veut négocier, nous sommes en position de force.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000440_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Though my power will be much diminished so far from the tower, it is a risk I am willing to take.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000440_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Mal<var 16 /var>heu<var 16 /var>reu<var 16 /var>se<var 16 /var>ment, je ne peux pas m'éloigner de la tour sans que ma santé en souffre.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000450_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Master Alphinaud─might I impose upon you to accompany me to Eulmore, prior to beginning your reconnaissance?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000450_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Alphinaud, pourrais-je te demander de m'aider étant donné que tu vas justement en Kholusia<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000460_ALPHINAUD<tab>Of course.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000460_ALPHINAUD<tab>Comptez sur moi<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000470_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Then let us make ready. Safe travels to you all.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000470_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Parfait<var 1D /var>! Préparons-nous pour le départ dans ce cas. Soyez prudents surtout<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000480_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>No matter how far he goes, man cannot resist looking back on the path he has walked.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000480_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Le passé lointain a toujours fasciné les contemporains.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000490_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>The untold stories and secrets of the past can be more alluring than the promise of tomorrow.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000490_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Car le chemin emprunté par les hommes pour atteindre l'instant présent est parfois plus mystérieux que l'avenir lui-même.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000500_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>And so he braves the forests of Rak'tika in search of mystery and wonder...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000500_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Les vestiges de l'ancienne civilisation de Ronka dormaient toujours dans cette luxuriante forêt.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000510_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Of Ronka, to which all seekers of hidden truths are inevitably drawn...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000510_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Un lieu où s'enfoncent les personnes en quête de réponses...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000520_URIANGER<tab>We have arrived.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000520_URIANGER<tab>Nous y sommes...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000530_URIANGER<tab>Vast though these woods may be, they are, by and large, uninhabitable.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000530_URIANGER<tab>Rak'tika est vaste, mais de nombreuses parties de la forêt sont impraticables et inhospitalières.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000540_URIANGER<tab>Not so the swamps of Citia, however, whose sparse foliage permitted man a foothold.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000540_URIANGER<tab>Les marécages du Citia sont parmi les endroits les moins hostiles. Voilà pourquoi le peuple de la Nuit s'y est installé.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000550_EMETSELCH<tab>"No lands must remain beyond our grasp. Go forth. Conquer. Rule.“
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000550_EMETSELCH<tab>“Si une terre s'étend sous vos yeux, à l'horizon, alors dévastez-la pour la subjuguer.”

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000560_EMETSELCH<tab>Forgive me. A sudden pang of nostalgia for those halcyon days.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000560_EMETSELCH<tab>Cette devise m'a permis de faire quelques voyages quand je jouais le rôle de Solus.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000570_EMETSELCH<tab>Exploring virgin territories, subjugating primitive peoples. All for the glory of Garlemald!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000570_EMETSELCH<tab>Invasions et conquêtes se succédaient, nation après nation. Oh comme il grandissait, mon bel empire<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000580_THANCRED<tab>If you've brought your ivory standard, I'll be happy to tell you where to stick it.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000580_THANCRED<tab>Il y en a pour qui ça a du mal à rentrer...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000590_EMETSELCH<tab>Can we not simply take a moment to enjoy the view together? Or would you rather I spied on you from the shadows?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000590_EMETSELCH<tab>Parle pour toi, imbécile. J'ai déjà expliqué gentiment que je n'étais là qu'en qualité d'observateur. Arrête d'aboyer à la première occasion.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000600_EMETSELCH<tab>Much more of this, and I may very well begin to regret my show of good faith.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000600_EMETSELCH<tab>Tu préfères sentir mon regard posé sur toi dans l'ombre<var 1D /var>? Aurais-tu du mal à comprendre que me manifester devant vous est une preuve de bonne volonté de ma part<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000610_RYNE<tab>If...if you really want to stay, then help us fight.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000610_RYNE<tab>Ça veut dire que vous allez nous accompagner... et vous battre à nos côtés<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000620_EMETSELCH<tab>Mmm... No, I think not. I am an observer─nothing more.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000620_EMETSELCH<tab>Disons que je vous suivrai aussi loin que bon me semble. Par contre, n'espérez pas me voir combattre.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000630_EMETSELCH<tab>Even shielded by the shadows of these boughs, I feel the Light's presence most keenly.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000630_EMETSELCH<tab>Des ombres douces se projettent dans la forêt, mais ne vous méprenez pas, elle baigne dans la Lumière comme les autres régions de ce monde.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000640_EMETSELCH<tab>To accompany you is taxing enough. To fight is out of the question.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000640_EMETSELCH<tab>Pour un Ascien comme moi, apôtre des Ténèbres, le simple fait de me trouver ici est déplaisant. Alors m'y battre<var 1D /var>? Pas question.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000650_THANCRED<tab>I will suffer your company if I must, but not your commentary.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000650_THANCRED<tab>Suis-nous si ça te chante, mais gare à toi si tu cherches à nous jouer des tours.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000660_URIANGER<tab>I see little sign of recent activity, nor hath any meaningful progress been made with the reconstruction...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000660_URIANGER<tab>Voici la forteresse de Gohn. Les réparations n'ont pas beaucoup avancé depuis la dernière fois...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000670_URIANGER<tab>Mayhap Y'shtola sought shelter elsewhere. Come, let us quit this place.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000670_URIANGER<tab>J'imagine que Y'shtola et les autres se sont installés ailleurs. Essayons de trouver où.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000680_RUNAR<tab>(-Blessed Leader-)Now! Surround them!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000680_RUNAR<tab>(-Homme à large carrure-)Encerclez-les<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000690_RUNAR<tab>(-Blessed Leader-)These sin eaters─they are not like the others!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000690_RUNAR<tab>(-Homme à large carrure-)... Ce sont eux les nouveaux purgateurs<var 1D /var>!? Mais on dirait des humains<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000700_THANCRED<tab>There's a reason for that. Lower your weapons, please. We mean you no harm.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000700_THANCRED<tab>“On dirait”<var 1D /var>? On est des humains comme vous<var 1D /var>! Alors si vous voulez bien baisser vos armes...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000710_PEOPLEOFNIGHTA<tab>How is it they can speak!?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000710_PEOPLEOFNIGHTA<tab>Les purgateurs parlent maintenant<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000720_PEOPLEOFNIGHTB<tab>It's a sin eater trick! They mean to kill us all!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000720_PEOPLEOFNIGHTB<tab>Vous laissez pas avoir<var 1D /var>! Ils imitent peut-être seulement nos voix<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_Q2_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>What will you say?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_Q2_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Que dites-vous<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A2_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Please! We're not sin eaters!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A2_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Puisqu'on vous dit qu'on est des humains<var 1D /var>!!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A2_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Uh... Kupo?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A2_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Kupopopo<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A2_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A2_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000730_PEOPLEOFNIGHTA<tab>Perhaps they speak the truth.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000730_PEOPLEOFNIGHTA<tab>Hé<var 1D /var>! Vous avez entendu<var 1D /var>? Ils se prétendent humains<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000740_THANCRED<tab>...That will seem a lot less amusing when we are forced to kill them.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000740_THANCRED<tab>... Arrêtez, c'est assez compliqué comme ça.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000750_EMETSELCH<tab>Oh, for the love of...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000750_EMETSELCH<tab>Mais j'y pense...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000760_EMETSELCH<tab>I had hoped that by accompanying you, we might come to understand one another, but all I have come to understand is that you have a knack for inflaming the natives.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000760_EMETSELCH<tab>Je me montre à vous par courtoisie, et j'ai déjà dit que je ne me battrai pas pour vous. Autrement dit, cette randonnée bucolique ne m'apporte rien.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000770_EMETSELCH<tab>You've committed the cardinal sin of <var 1A 02 /var>boring<var 1A 01 /var> me. And so I retire to the shade.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000770_EMETSELCH<tab>Et pour être tout à fait honnête, je commence sé<var 16 /var>rieu<var 16 /var>se<var 16 /var>ment à m'ennuyer. Je ferais bien une petite sieste au pied d'un arbre... Oui, je crois que je vais faire ça<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000780_EMETSELCH<tab>Good luck.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000780_EMETSELCH<tab>À plus tard<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000790_PEOPLEOFNIGHTA<tab>There! Did you see that one disappear!?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000790_PEOPLEOFNIGHTA<tab>Y-y en a un qui a disparu<var 1D /var>! Je savais qu'ils étaient louches<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000800_THANCRED<tab>(SIGH)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000800_THANCRED<tab>(Soupire)

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000810_THANCRED<tab>I think I preferred Lahabrea.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000810_THANCRED<tab>Pour un type qui s'ennuie, il nous en attire des ennuis<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000820_YSHTOLA<tab>(-???-)Enough. Runar, report.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000820_YSHTOLA<tab>(-Voix familière-)Quel vacarme... Alors, ces purgateurs<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000830_RUNAR<tab>Master Matoya!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000830_RUNAR<tab>(-Homme à large carrure-)Matoya<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000840_RUNAR<tab>We apprehended them as you ordered, but...are you certain these are sin eaters?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000840_RUNAR<tab>(-Homme à large carrure-)Ils ressemblent à s'y méprendre à des humains... Vous êtes sûre que ce sont des purgateurs<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000850_YSHTOLA<tab>The intense light of the aether I saw was unmistakable. If not sin eaters, then what?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000850_YSHTOLA<tab>Quoi d'autre<var 1D /var>? Je ne les ai pas vus de près, mais une forte Lumière émane d'eux.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000860_URIANGER<tab>'Tis passing queer that Y'shtola should mistake us for the enemy, is it not?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000860_URIANGER<tab>Je ne vous apprends rien, mais Y'shtola a perdu la vue dans un accident il y a quelque temps...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000870_URIANGER<tab>Mayhap it hath been too long since last she beheld the radiance of thine aether...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000870_URIANGER<tab>Elle ressent maintenant l'éther qui émane de chaque chose, mais sa perception est restée aussi fine qu'avant. Enfin, en théorie...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000880_URIANGER<tab>Master Matoya. Hath time truly made strangers of us?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000880_URIANGER<tab>Maître Matoya... Vous m'avez forcément reconnu. C'est moi, Urianger.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000890_YSHTOLA<tab>Nay. I recognize you, Urianger, Thancred. And this is Minfilia of the First, of whom you spoke before.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000890_YSHTOLA<tab>Effectivement... c'est bien toi. Je reconnais également Thancred. Et j'imagine que cette personne à tes côtés est la Minfilia de ce monde, dont j'ai déjà entendu parler<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000900_URIANGER<tab>Just so. And knowing as thou must that we come in peace, might I prevail upon thee to have thy comrades lower their arms?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000900_URIANGER<tab>Vous avez vu juste...Pourriez-vous baisser vos armes maintenant<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000910_YSHTOLA<tab>First explain this other presence in your company. The one I know not.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000910_YSHTOLA<tab>Juste une chose... Je veux bien admettre que tu sois le véritable Urianger, mais quelle est cette créature<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000920_YSHTOLA<tab>There is but one manner of creature in this world whose aether is suffused with such an abundance of light.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000920_YSHTOLA<tab>Elle déborde de Lumière, tel un purgateur...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000930_URIANGER<tab>Mine apologies, Master Matoya, but thou art mistaken. Before thee standeth our dearest comrade. The truest hero among us.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000930_URIANGER<tab>Ne me dites pas que vous avez déjà oublié <var 08 E905 ((l'héroïne)) ((le héros)) /var> des Héritiers de la Septième Aube....

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000940_URIANGER<tab>Though he is but recently arrived here in the First, not one but <var 1A 02 /var>two<var 1A 01 /var> Lightwardens have already perished by his most puissant hand.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000940_URIANGER<tab>Notre ami a déjà terrassé deux grands purgateurs depuis son arrivée.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000950_URIANGER<tab>Though she is but recently arrived here in the First, not one but <var 1A 02 /var>two<var 1A 01 /var> Lightwardens have already perished by her most puissant hand.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000950_URIANGER<tab>Notre amie a déjà terrassé deux grands purgateurs depuis son arrivée.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000960_YSHTOLA<tab>It... It cannot be!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000960_YSHTOLA<tab>C'est... C'est vraiment toi<var 1D /var>!?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_Q3_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>What will you say?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_Q3_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Que répondez-vous à Y'shtola<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A3_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>It's been too long...clearly.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A3_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Ça faisait un sacré bout de temps qu'on ne s'était pas vu<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var>s<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A3_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Nice to see you too...“Master Matoya.”
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A3_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>“Matoya”, hein<var 1D /var>? J'ai toujours trouvé que c'était un joli prénom...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A3_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>You truly thought me a sin eater?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A3_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>En chair et en os, mais un peu vexé<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var>...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000970_RUNAR<tab>Master Matoya?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000970_RUNAR<tab>(-Homme à large carrure-)Matoya... Qu'est-ce qu'on fait alors<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000980_YSHTOLA<tab>Lower your weapons.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000980_YSHTOLA<tab>Désolée, j'ai fait erreur... Baissez vos armes.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000990_YSHTOLA<tab>Forgive us this hostile welcome.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_000990_YSHTOLA<tab>Je m'excuse pour cet accueil un peu brutal.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001000_YSHTOLA<tab>Come, I would give you a proper introduction to Rak'tika and its people.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001000_YSHTOLA<tab>Bienvenue à Rak'tika... Le peuple de la Nuit est heureux de vous y recevoir.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001010_YSHTOLA<tab>Slitherbough is the largest of the Blessed's settlements.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001010_YSHTOLA<tab>Voici Serpentige, notre plus grand hameau.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001020_YSHTOLA<tab>They worship no gods, instead revering Darkness itself.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001020_YSHTOLA<tab>Les membres de cette communauté vouent un culte aux Ténèbres, mais ils n'ont pas spé<var 16 /var>cia<var 16 /var>le<var 16 /var>ment de dieux. Ils suivent leur propre dogme et passent leurs journées dans le calme de la prière.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001030_YSHTOLA<tab>It is a curious kind of faith, but one which has granted them the strength to persevere in the wake of the Flood.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001030_YSHTOLA<tab>Grâce à ce quotidien, ils ont acquis les con<var 16 /var>nais<var 16 /var>san<var 16 /var>ces nécessaires pour survivre dans ce monde après le déluge de Lumière.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001040_YSHTOLA<tab>I hope you weren't expecting a grand feast by way of welcome. They are a simple people.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001040_YSHTOLA<tab>Ces gens font vœu de pauvreté. Ne t'attends pas à un accueil luxueux.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001050_YSHTOLA<tab>Now, I would hear of your travels away from prying ears. Come.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001050_YSHTOLA<tab>Bien, vous allez pouvoir me raconter un peu ce qu'il s'est passé de votre côté. Mais mieux vaut éviter d'en parler ici... Allons dans la salle au fond.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001060_YSHTOLA<tab>I see. And now you seek the Lightwarden of Rak'tika.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001060_YSHTOLA<tab>Je vois... Et vous êtes donc ici pour chasser le grand purgateur de Rak'tika.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001070_YSHTOLA<tab>In the days after I arrived in the First, I too relied upon the Crystal Exarch for guidance. But his penchant for secrecy and the telling of half-truths soon lost him my trust. And thus did I strike out on my own.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001070_YSHTOLA<tab>Moi, j'ai passé le plus clair de mon temps à me renseigner sur l'histoire du premier reflet. Je n'irais pas jusqu'à dire que je n'ai aucune confiance en l'exarque, mais il est dangereux de faire de lui notre seule source d'in<var 16 /var>for<var 16 /var>ma<var 16 /var>tions.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001080_YSHTOLA<tab>My work eventually led me here to the forest, which I have come to know like the back of my hand.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001080_YSHTOLA<tab>Voilà ce qui m'a menée dans ce hameau, que je connais maintenant comme ma poche.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001090_YSHTOLA<tab>I cannot say with certainty where your quarry is hiding, but I am confident I can narrow the search.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001090_YSHTOLA<tab>Pour résumer, je n'ai toujours pas localisé le grand purgateur, mais j'en sais assez pour soupçonner certaines zones en particulier.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001100_THANCRED<tab>Well...go on, then.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001100_THANCRED<tab>C'est-à-dire<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001110_YSHTOLA<tab>Some few thousand years ago, this forest stood at the heart of the empire of Ronka.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001110_YSHTOLA<tab>Il y a plusieurs millénaires, Rak'tika était le cœur de l'empire ronka.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001120_YSHTOLA<tab>A great many relics of that civilization can still be found to the east in Yx'Maja.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001120_YSHTOLA<tab>Aujourd'hui encore, il n'est pas rare de tomber sur des vestiges de cette civilisation en se promenant à l'est, dans la forêt d'Yx'Maja.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001130_YSHTOLA<tab>Or rather, <var 1A 02 /var>could<var 1A 01 /var> be found─were the area not fiercely guarded.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001130_YSHTOLA<tab>Et aussi étrange que cela puisse paraître, ils sont en assez bon état. C'est grâce aux gardiennes, qui les protègent depuis toujours.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001140_YSHTOLA<tab>Yx'Maja, you see, is home to a tribe of warriors whose lineage is said to date back to the time of the empire. Any attempt to enter their territory is met with lethal force. They offer no warnings, and suffer no trespasser to escape.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001140_YSHTOLA<tab>Elles ne tolèrent la présence d'aucun intrus. Impossible de négocier, elles attaquent à vue.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001150_YSHTOLA<tab>Needless to say, my every attempt to survey the area has been thwarted.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001150_YSHTOLA<tab>J'ai évidemment tenté de m'infiltrer dans leur forêt à plusieurs reprises, mais c'est plus facile à dire qu'à faire quand on est assaillie de toutes parts.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001160_URIANGER<tab>Mayhap the Warden hideth there full knowing none may approach it for fear of these protectors.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001160_URIANGER<tab>Ce qui signifie qu'un grand purgateur pourrait facilement se terrer dans la forêt d'Yx'Maja, sur le territoire protégé par les Viis.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001170_YSHTOLA<tab>As for the tablet...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001170_YSHTOLA<tab>Un cadeau de la part de l'exarque...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001180_YSHTOLA<tab>I find the timing of its discovery suspiciously convenient. If I did not know better, I would think someone was trying to curry favor with me.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001180_YSHTOLA<tab>Hpmf... Il pensait sûrement que cette tablette ronka allait me convaincre de vous aider à réaliser son plan.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001190_YSHTOLA<tab>Regardless, it will take time to decipher these writings. Yet I would not be at all surprised if they somehow held the key to entering Yx'Maja unmolested. The Exarch has a nose for serendipity.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001190_YSHTOLA<tab>Quoi qu'il en soit, ça vaut la peine d'essayer de la déchiffrer. Il va falloir trouver un moyen de pénétrer dans la forêt...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001200_URIANGER<tab>If there is aught I can do to assist thee in unraveling their secrets, thou need'st only ask.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001200_URIANGER<tab>Je ne vous serai sans doute pas d'une grande aide, mais je me tiens à votre disposition.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001210_YSHTOLA<tab>Thank you, Urianger. I may well take you up on that offer.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001210_YSHTOLA<tab>Ma foi en tes capacités est in<var 16 /var>é<var 16 /var>bran<var 16 /var>la<var 16 /var>ble.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001220_YSHTOLA<tab>While we set to work, might I suggest you take a tour of the city?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001220_YSHTOLA<tab>Que dirais-tu de visiter Serpentige pendant ce temps<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001230_YSHTOLA<tab>Should you be in any doubt as to the importance of your role as the “Warrior of Darkness,” the people here will surely cure you of it.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001230_YSHTOLA<tab>Un événement lourd de sens pour <var 08 E905 ((la Guerrière)) ((le Guerrier)) /var> des Ténèbres va bientôt avoir lieu.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001240_THANCRED<tab>I must say, Y'shtola...while most of us have struggled to come to terms with our altered circumstances, you seem to have adapted rather well.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001240_THANCRED<tab>Comme c'est étrange... Tu as presque l'air plus vivante ici que chez nous<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001250_YSHTOLA<tab>Lest you forget, Master Matoya and I dedicated our lives to uncovering the truth which hides at the heart of our world.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001250_YSHTOLA<tab>C'est normal. Mon maître et moi, nous avons toujours voulu élucider le mystère autour de l'origine de notre monde.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001260_YSHTOLA<tab>Though separate, the fate of this reflection is nevertheless bound to that of our home. That I would be daunted by such an invaluable opportunity is absurd.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001260_YSHTOLA<tab>Ce voyage vers un reflet, c'est une chance inespérée d'en savoir plus. Ce que je découvre chaque jour me fascine et me stimule<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001270_YSHTOLA<tab>But what of you, Thancred? Could it be that you are still struggling to “come to terms” with the nature of your young companion?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001270_YSHTOLA<tab>Pas toi, Thancred<var 1D /var>? Tu n'es pas heureux d'avoir retrouvé ta petite princesse<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001280_THANCRED<tab>My “struggles” are none of your concern. Quite why you would speak thus─and in <var 1A 02 /var>this<var 1A 01 /var> company─I do not know. Perhaps you left more of yourself back in the Source than I assumed. If you'll excuse me.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001280_THANCRED<tab>Les persiflages ne te siéent guère, Y'shtola. Nous ne sommes plus des enfants. Sur ce, j'ai une enquête à mener.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001290_RYNE<tab>He understands that I'm not the same. That I'm not her.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001290_RYNE<tab>Euh... Vous vous trompez, vous savez<var 1D /var>? Je ne suis pas la vraie Minfilia aux yeux de Thancred.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001300_YSHTOLA<tab>Understands, perhaps, but does not accept. The question being whether he ever will.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001300_YSHTOLA<tab>C'est facile de se trouver des excuses lorsque les choses ne se passent pas comme prévu. L'important, c'est de savoir réagir quand ça arrive.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001310_YSHTOLA<tab>And whether <var 1A 02 /var>you<var 1A 01 /var> will, more importantly. As difficult as your circumstances may be, they are yours, not his. 'Tis you and you alone who bears ultimate responsibility for your life.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001310_YSHTOLA<tab>Surtout quand on sait que les con<var 16 /var>sé<var 16 /var>quen<var 16 /var>ces peuvent être gravissimes. Repoussez l'échéance tant que vous voudrez, personne ne viendra faire le travail à votre place.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001320_YSHTOLA<tab>But you need not make any hard choices now. Why not go and get some fresh air─clear your head?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001320_YSHTOLA<tab>Va faire un tour, toi aussi. Découvrir de nouvelles choses t'aidera peut-être à réfléchir.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001330_YSHTOLA<tab>It seemed only right that we show our faces. May we join you?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001330_YSHTOLA<tab>Nous nous devions d'assister à la cérémonie...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001340_RUNAR<tab>Let us begin.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001340_RUNAR<tab>Commençons...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001350_RUNAR<tab>I thank you all for coming to pay respects to our fallen daughter of the night. In the light, she was known as Toddia. But in the dark, we shall remember her always as Minnine. Let us each take a moment to offer her our prayers.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001350_RUNAR<tab>Toddia était notre amie à tous. Et la Lumière n'aura jamais terni son véritable nom<var 1D /var>: Minnine... Prions pour elle...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001360_RUNAR<tab>We entrust her now to the night's sweet embrace.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001360_RUNAR<tab>Que ton existence retourne à la mer, ténébreuse et céleste...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001370_RUNAR<tab>In Darkness will she be free from pain and suffering, now and forevermore.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001370_RUNAR<tab>Les épreuves restent avec nous, ici-bas. Pour toi, plus de douleur ni de peur.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001380_RUNAR<tab>May her soul find peace in the sunless sea of heaven, and in the love we bear for her in our hearts.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001380_RUNAR<tab>Que cette mer remplisse nos êtres de son doux silence et d'un chaleureux amour. Que nos pensées t'ac<var 16 /var>com<var 16 /var>pa<var 16 /var>gnent à travers nos prières...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001390_YSHTOLA<tab>That vessel represents the night sky. The “sunless sea of heaven.”
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001390_YSHTOLA<tab>Cet objet représente le ciel étoilé. C'est leur mer céleste à eux...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001400_RUNAR<tab>We call upon you now, O Bringer of Shadow, to lead this gentle soul unto the sea. We call upon you, O Warrior of Darkness, to deliver her unto paradise everlasting.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001400_RUNAR<tab>Emmène cette âme rejoindre les ténèbres des cieux, messager de la Nuit... Guerrier des Ténèbres...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001410_YSHTOLA<tab>I am told you assisted in the preparations for the service. On behalf of the Blessed, you have my sincerest thanks.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001410_YSHTOLA<tab>On m'a dit que tu avais participé à la préparation de la cérémonie. Ça me va droit au cœur.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001420_YSHTOLA<tab>The enduring legend of the Warrior of Darkness owes much to the traditions of these people.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001420_YSHTOLA<tab>Ces histoires que l'on raconte aux quatre coins de ce monde sur le Guerrier des Ténèbres, elles puisent leur source dans les prières du peuple de la Nuit.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001430_YSHTOLA<tab>And none were more ardent in their faith than Toddia. She would have been greatly moved by your presence.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001430_YSHTOLA<tab>Toddia était dévote. Je pense qu'elle est heureuse que ce soit toi, <var 08 E905 ((la Guerrière)) ((le Guerrier)) /var> des Ténèbres, qui la trouve et l'accompagne jusqu'au bout.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_Q4_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>What will you say?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_Q4_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Que répondez-vous à Y'shtola<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A4_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>I should like to have met her.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A4_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Je l'espère...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A4_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>You know I don't deserve such reverence.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A4_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Je n'ai pourtant rien fait...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A4_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_A4_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001440_RYNE<tab>You might not deliver her to the heavens, but if you could deliver the night sky to her people─the <var 1A 02 /var>real<var 1A 01 /var> night sky─it would be the next best thing.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001440_RYNE<tab>Ce n'est pas à prendre au pied de la lettre. Ces gens croient juste que s'ils ont un jour la chance d'admirer le ciel étoilé, leurs défunts le sauront.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001450_RYNE<tab>Their prayers would finally be answered. They could gaze up at the firmament and see their ancestors in every twinkle of the stars.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001450_RYNE<tab>Leurs prières ont été entendues. La preuve de leur existence subsiste encore aujourd'hui, devant nous.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001460_RYNE<tab>We cannot allow their hopes and dreams to drown in the light. We have to bring back the dark. If we don't, who will?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001460_RYNE<tab>C'est pour ça que... je ferai tout pour que leurs espoirs ne soient pas anéantis. Je vaincrai les grands purgateurs qui les menacent<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001470_RYNE<tab>Forgive me. Thinking of all those we have lost, I...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001470_RYNE<tab>Oh, euh... Désolée... Je ne voulais pas vous ennuyer avec mes histoires.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001480_THANCRED<tab>No, it's all right. We <var 1A 02 /var>will<var 1A 01 /var> bring back the dark.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001480_THANCRED<tab>Non, c'est une noble envie. Ensemble, nous offrirons la nuit aux membres de cette communauté.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001490_YSHTOLA<tab>Mayhap sooner than later, in fact.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001490_YSHTOLA<tab>En parlant de ça, je suis sur le point d'extraire de la tablette des in<var 16 /var>for<var 16 /var>ma<var 16 /var>tions qui pourraient nous y aider.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001500_YSHTOLA<tab>Urianger and I have finished deciphering the tablet, and its contents were most illuminating. Let us reconvene in my chambers. We have much to discuss.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001500_YSHTOLA<tab>Ça promet d'être intéressant. Rejoignez-moi où nous avons discuté tout à l'heure.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001510_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>These paintings...they seem familiar. Depictions of heroes throughout history. The age of gods... The empire of Ronka... And this...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001510_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Ce sont les portraits des héros d'une autre époque. Le temps des dieux, celui de la civilisation de Ronka...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001520_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>There was a man. A researcher who pored over these pieces...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001520_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Autrefois, quand j'étais encore de ce monde, des gens étaient entrés dans la grotte. Ils voulaient y étudier les fresques.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001530_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>He offered us work when we needed it. Slaying beasts, delivering provisions... A funny old bugger, he was, but he had a good heart.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001530_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>On m'a alors confié quelques missions<var 1D /var>: tuer des monstres, apporter des ra<var 16 /var>vi<var 16 /var>tail<var 16 /var>le<var 16 /var>ments... ce genre de choses. Ils avaient quelque chose d'étrange, ces gens. Mais avec le temps, on a commencé à bien s'entendre.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001540_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>He believed this first painting dated back to a time of myth and legends. A tribute to the heroes of a long-forgotten era.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001540_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>D'après eux, c'était des portraits peints par des inconnus à une époque si reculée que leurs noms étaient tombés dans l'oubli. Il s'agissait des héros qui les avaient guidés.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001550_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>The story went that it was rediscovered by an explorer from Ronka, who was so struck by its majesty that a second painting was commissioned, commemorating the heroes of their day.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001550_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Puis le temps a passé, et quelqu'un a redécouvert cet endroit à l'ère ronka. On a alors ajouté le portrait d'autres héros juste à côté.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001560_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>"One day, you will all be here too,“ he said. ”Heroes immortalized forever. Maybe I'll paint you myself!“
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001560_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>“Quand vous serez célèbres dans le monde entier, faudra qu'on ajoute vos têtes aussi<var 1D /var>!”

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001570_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>I had a good laugh at that. We were only trying to make our way, after all. Being heroes couldn't have been further from our minds.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001570_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Ils nous ont dit ça, hilares. La bonne blague. On était surtout leurs larbins...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001580_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>But it seems...he actually went and did it. Before or after the Flood, I wonder...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001580_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Ça, je crois que c'est le portrait qu'ils ont fait de nous. Ils ont tenu parole...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001590_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Rather faded, isn't it, compared to the others. Or did someone try to scrape it off the wall? Maybe the man himself, once he came to his senses...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001590_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Je me demande si les dégâts datent d'avant ou d'après le Déluge... J'espère en tout cas que ce sont les archéologues qui ont dégradé notre fresque. Je comprendrais...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001600_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Do you suppose your deeds will warrant an addition to this collection? Or some other kind of monument?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001600_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Et toi, comment crois-tu que ton combat sera transmis aux générations futures<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001610_YSHTOLA<tab>There you are. I have everything I need. Let us quit this place.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001610_YSHTOLA<tab>Je n'ai pas été trop longue<var 1D /var>? J'ai fini en tout cas. Ne restons pas un instant de plus ici.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001620_YSHTOLA<tab>Is something the matter? We should go. The others are waiting.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001620_YSHTOLA<tab>Qu'est-ce qu'il y a<var 1D /var>? Il faut vraiment qu'on y aille. Thancred nous attend à l'extérieur.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001630_RUNAR<tab>Strange...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001630_RUNAR<tab>La forêt est un peu agitée, aujourd'hui.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001640_RUNAR<tab>The others on patrol should have returned by now. Our food will be overcooked if we wait any longer.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001640_RUNAR<tab>La patrouille n'est toujours pas rentrée...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001650_RUNAR<tab>We will just have to start without them. Would you call Master Matoya and the others?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001650_RUNAR<tab>Tant pis, on n'a qu'à commencer sans eux. Tu veux bien aller chercher les autres<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001660_YSHTOLA<tab>I tire of these games, Urianger. Why do you pretend you cannot see it!?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001660_YSHTOLA<tab>N'élude pas la question. Toi aussi, tu as remarqué, non<var 1D /var>!?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001670_YSHTOLA<tab>The blessing may spare <var 08 E905 ((her)) ((him)) /var> the fate of becoming a Lightwarden...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001670_YSHTOLA<tab><var 08 E905 ((Elle)) ((Il)) /var> a la bénédiction de la Lumière. Ça veut dire qu'<var 08 E905 ((elle)) ((il)) /var> peut vaincre un grand purgateur sans risquer d'en devenir un... Je suis certaine d'en avoir entendu parler<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001680_YSHTOLA<tab>But you cannot be blind to the nascent corruption! <var 08 E905 ((She)) ((He)) /var> is not as <var 08 E905 ((she)) ((he)) /var> was in the Source.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001680_YSHTOLA<tab>Mais si c'est le cas, pourquoi son éther est-il dans cet état-là<var 1D /var>? Je sais que la situation n'est pas encore dramatique, mais on ne peut pas non plus dire que tout va bien.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001690_YSHTOLA<tab>Though I have no proof, I fear that the light which poured forth from the Wardens was not negated at all.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001690_YSHTOLA<tab>Arrête-moi si je me trompe, mais la bénédiction de la Lumière lui permet seulement d'absorber la Lumière des grands purgateurs, pas de la neutraliser, non<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001700_YSHTOLA<tab>I fear it was <var 1A 02 /var>absorbed<var 1A 01 /var>─that <var 08 E905 ((she)) ((he)) /var> has been suffused with their light.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001700_YSHTOLA<tab>Elle est juste retenue au fond <var 08 E905 ((d'elle)) ((de lui)) /var>. Pas vrai<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001710_URIANGER<tab>Though I have given thought to this possibility, I dare not speak until more is known.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001710_URIANGER<tab>Je crois savoir comment régler le problème une bonne fois pour toutes, mais ce n'est ni l'heure ni l'endroit pour en discuter.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001720_YSHTOLA<tab>(SIGH)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001720_YSHTOLA<tab>(Soupire)

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001730_YSHTOLA<tab>By the time you deign to enlighten us, it may be too late─if it is not already.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001730_YSHTOLA<tab>Ton entêtement me désole. Le temps presse et tu refuses de parler...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001740_YSHTOLA<tab>Urianger─I know full well, after all these years, that you have only the best of intentions.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001740_YSHTOLA<tab>Urianger, je ne pense pas que tu agisses dans l'intention de nous nuire.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001750_YSHTOLA<tab>But that does not make it any easier to put my faith in a man so infatuated with secrecy.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001750_YSHTOLA<tab>Mais avec toutes ces cachotteries, ça va vraiment être difficile de t'accorder la même confiance qu'avant.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001760_YSHTOLA<tab>I have had my suspicions ever since the Exarch bade you speak that day, but now I must ask.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001760_YSHTOLA<tab>Tu sais, il y a une chose qui me chiffonne depuis que nous sommes arrivés ici.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001770_YSHTOLA<tab>The Eighth Umbral Calamity and all that followed; everything you claimed to have seen─did you?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001770_YSHTOLA<tab>C'est ta vision du huitième fléau qui a provoqué tout ça, mais est-ce réellement ce que tu as vu lorsque nous avons été invoqués dans ce monde<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001780_PEOPLEOFNIGHTA<tab>Help! Someone help!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001780_PEOPLEOFNIGHTA<tab>À... À l'aide<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001790_PEOPLEOFNIGHTA<tab>The Eulmorans have come for us! We're under attack!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001790_PEOPLEOFNIGHTA<tab>C'est l'armée d'Eulmore<var 1D /var>! Elle nous attaque<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001800_SYSTEM_NONE_VOICE<tab>Meanwhile, in Eulmore...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001800_SYSTEM_NONE_VOICE<tab>Pendant ce temps, dans les quartiers du gouverneur à Eulmore

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001810_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Lord Vauthry, how good it is to see you. How long has it been? Not since your inauguration, unless I am mistaken? Too long, at any rate. May I say how humbled I am to be invited not only into your city, but your home. You are as generous as ever.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001810_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>À quand remonte notre dernière rencontre<var 1D /var>? Après votre intronisation, non<var 1D /var>? Regardez-moi cette... carrure<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001820_VAUTHRY<tab>And you as disingenuous.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001820_VAUTHRY<tab>Hum... Tu t'autorises quelques désagréables familiarités, Exarque.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001830_VAUTHRY<tab>Let us dispense with the pleasantries. This merry band of dissidents people are calling “Warriors of Darkness”... They have slain sin eaters, and by all accounts the Crystarium is complicit in their villainy.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001830_VAUTHRY<tab>Alors comme ça, Cristarium prêterait main-forte à je ne sais quels Guerriers des Ténèbres pour assassiner les purgateurs...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001840_VAUTHRY<tab>And now I hear reports of your people obstructing my soldiers. So I must ask: what exactly do you think you are doing?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001840_VAUTHRY<tab>Et en plus, vous vous seriez également montrés impolis envers mon armée... Puis-je savoir ce que cela signifie<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001850_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>I might ask you the same thing. It should be clear even to you that defeating the Lightwardens represents the world's only hope of survival.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001850_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>C'est moi qui suis venu vous poser quelques questions, Don Vauthry... Et si je puis me permettre, chacun ici-bas espère voir disparaître les grands purgateurs.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001860_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Even now, the people of Lakeland and Il Mheg rejoice in the return of night.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001860_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>C'est le cas pour tous les habitants de Grand-Lac évidemment, mais également pour le peuple féérique. Tous voient d'un bon œil le retour des Ténèbres.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001870_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>For a hundred years, they yearned for a means to fight back against the sin eaters and at last they have found one. Yet you choose to stand idly by and do nothing. Why?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001870_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>C'est le signe que la révolte a commencé. Celui que l'humanité attendait. Pourquoi s'y opposer<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001880_VAUTHRY<tab>Why? Because this “hope” you cling to is nothing more than a fever dream. An exercise in futility.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001880_VAUTHRY<tab>Tu ne comprends rien. Tu ne comprends rien de rien, Exarque. Tes espoirs sont sans lendemain<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001890_VAUTHRY<tab>Even should you slay the sin eaters, the world as we know it is beyond salvation.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001890_VAUTHRY<tab>Même si vous parveniez à vaincre les purgateurs, le monde ne se remettrait jamais des dégâts causés par le Déluge.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001900_VAUTHRY<tab>With what little land and resources remain, the people would be free only to starve.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001900_VAUTHRY<tab>Il ne reste pas assez de ressources pour tout le monde.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001910_VAUTHRY<tab>Before long they would turn to violence, then to war, and ultimately usher themselves unto oblivion.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001910_VAUTHRY<tab>Bientôt, des rixes éclateront. La population diminuera inéluctablement, et l'humanité s'éteindra.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001920_VAUTHRY<tab>They require a firm hand to shepherd them from the edge. The hand of a king─nay, a god!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001920_VAUTHRY<tab>C'est pour ça que je dois prendre la situation en main. M'imposer en roi<var 1D /var>! Que dis-je... en dieu<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001930_VAUTHRY<tab>I will see their dreams fulfilled, their wishes granted. I will give them peace, order─and they shall never want for bliss.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001930_VAUTHRY<tab>Ils seront à mes pieds, et je les ferai rêver<var 1D /var>! Je serai l'ordre et la paix<var 1D /var>! Je serai leur seule et unique source de joie<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001940_VAUTHRY<tab>Men are fickle creatures who entertain vague ideals without the faintest notion what they cost. But a little fear can go a long way towards helping them realize what it is they truly need.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001940_VAUTHRY<tab>Cher Exarque... Les gens sont stupides. Leurs idéaux n'engendrent que des divergences. Il faut leur inspirer un minimum de terreur pour les guider.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001950_VAUTHRY<tab><var 1A 02 /var>Sanctuary<var 1A 01 /var>. And they shall find none in this world, save that which <var 1A 02 /var>I<var 1A 01 /var> afford them.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001950_VAUTHRY<tab>Il n'y a qu'auprès de moi qu'ils seront en sécurité. Il n'y a qu'auprès de moi qu'ils pourront vivre.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001960_VAUTHRY<tab>That is why the sin eaters exist. To unite the world under <var 1A 02 /var>my<var 1A 01 /var> dominion!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001960_VAUTHRY<tab>Voilà pourquoi les purgateurs existent. C'est un don que ce monde m'a fait pour que je règne, par la force si nécessaire<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001970_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>A paradise fit to grace the Eighth Umbral Era.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001970_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Je vois... Et un tel royaume aurait facilement vu le jour dans un monde meurtri par le huitième fléau...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001980_VAUTHRY<tab>What was that?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001980_VAUTHRY<tab>Hum<var 1D /var>? Plaît-il<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001990_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>A minor epiphany, nothing more.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_001990_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>N'y prêtez pas attention, je me parlais à moi-même. J'ai compris vos motivations, c'est l'essentiel.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002000_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>You have always held sway over those around you. Those who defy you must submit or die. What sits before me is the inevitable result of bloated privilege and unchecked power.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002000_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Don Vauthry, vous avez toujours utilisé la force dont vous disposiez pour asservir les hommes... Un com<var 16 /var>por<var 16 /var>te<var 16 /var>ment plus ou moins logique quand on n'a jamais rencontré plus fort que soi.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002010_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>But man is more resilient than you think.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002010_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Mais l'humanité est plus coriace et rusée que vous le croyez.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002020_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>His achievements are not the product of violence and bloodshed but compassion and understanding.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002020_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Les hommes n'usurperont pas aux autres ce dont ils manquent. Ils le produiront... C'est comme ça que sont nées leurs techniques et leurs con<var 16 /var>nais<var 16 /var>san<var 16 /var>ces approfondies.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002030_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>This calamity is but another crisis to be overcome. And we will─once we eliminate the sin eaters.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002030_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Ça prendra le temps que ça prendra, mais ils surmonteront les obstacles. Et c'est pour ça qu'il nous faut vaincre les purgateurs.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002040_VAUTHRY<tab>You poor, deluded fool. These people care not for the morrow. They care only for the now, and the contentment they lack. What good is a paradise to them if it is a thousand years in the making? Or even a hundred!?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002040_VAUTHRY<tab>Sornettes<var 1D /var>! Ce que les gens veulent, ici et maintenant, c'est leur propre bonheur. Que vaut le paradis s'il n'ouvre ses portes que dans un siècle, voire un millénaire<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002050_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>You underestimate them, Lord Vauthry. They see further than you think. I have beheld it in the blood and sweat and tears of those who would sacrifice everything for a future they may never know. That their children may never know.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002050_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Certes, mais je l'ai pourtant constaté de mes yeux. J'ai vu des personnes en pousser d'autres vers l'avant, versant sang et larmes pour elles, pour un avenir meilleur qu'elles-mêmes ne connaîtraient jamais.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002060_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>I have beheld it in the hopes and dreams of those who came before, which we bequeath to those who come after, that they might in turn build upon the foundations laid by our forebears.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002060_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Elles luttaient, malgré le poids qui les accablait et la douleur des au revoir, car elles savaient que tout cela avait un sens.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002070_MYSTERYVOICE<tab><var 1A 02 /var>These<var 1A 01 /var> are the bonds which hold man and his world together, not your gilded chains─and I will resist your every effort to shackle him.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002070_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Cette expérience m'a appris de quoi était fait un monde... Voilà pourquoi je donnerais ma vie pour briser la fatalité.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002080_VAUTHRY<tab>In summary, you will continue to support the villains hunting my sin eaters?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002080_VAUTHRY<tab>J'en déduis que vous continuerez à chasser les purgateurs<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002090_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>With tremendous enthusiasm, for I have faith in the future they would build.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002090_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Oui, et j'ai hâte de voir un jour s'ouvrir la voie vers un avenir meilleur. Le jour où tout le monde, <var 08 E905 ((cette femme la première)) ((cet homme le premier)) /var>, foulera ce chemin.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002100_VAUTHRY<tab>Why do I even bother?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002100_VAUTHRY<tab>(soupire) Décidément...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002110_VAUTHRY<tab>Fools, the lot of you! So naive! So <var 1A 02 /var>painfully<var 1A 01 /var> predictable!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002110_VAUTHRY<tab>Tu crois que je ne me doutais pas de ta réponse<var 1D /var>!? Je savais que je traitais avec une belle bande d'abrutis...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002120_VAUTHRY<tab>Did you imagine I did not know your mind? That I would wait until <var 1A 02 /var>after<var 1A 01 /var> this meeting to dispatch my forces!? Even as we speak, they march to the sin eaters' defense!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002120_VAUTHRY<tab>Je n'ai pas attendu cette rencontre pour envoyer mes troupes vers les territoires encore baignés de Lumière.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002130_VAUTHRY<tab>Insurrection will not be tolerated!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002130_VAUTHRY<tab>Elles protégeront les derniers grands purgateurs et éradiqueront quiconque osera s'en prendre à eux<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002140_VAUTHRY<tab>The people of this world are mine to rule, mine to command...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002140_VAUTHRY<tab>D'ailleurs, ce n'est pas pour papoter que je t'ai fait venir jusqu'ici...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002150_VAUTHRY<tab>And you are no exception!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002150_VAUTHRY<tab>C'est pour faire de toi mon pantin<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002160_VAUTHRY<tab>What!? How did he─
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002160_VAUTHRY<tab>Où... Où est-il passé<var 1D /var>!?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002170_VAUTHRY<tab>Insolent swine! I will not stand for this. Do you hear me!?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002170_VAUTHRY<tab>Une illusion<var 1D /var>!? Ils se moquent vraiment tous de moi<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002180_VAUTHRY<tab>(SCREAM)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002180_VAUTHRY<tab>ぎぃぃぃ！

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002190_RANJIT<tab>You speak for the Night's Blessed?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002190_RANJIT<tab>Vous parlez au nom du peuple de la Nuit<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002200_YSHTOLA<tab>I do.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002200_YSHTOLA<tab>Oui, et j'imagine que vous avez deux ou trois choses à me dire...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002210_YSHTOLA<tab>I presume <var 1A 02 /var>that<var 1A 01 /var> is your doing.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002210_YSHTOLA<tab>Comme ce que vous avez fait à ce malheureux, par exemple<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002220_YSHTOLA<tab>If you have come to parley, I must insist that you first return him to us.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002220_YSHTOLA<tab>Si vous voulez que notre discussion se passe sans heurt, je vous conseille de nous le rendre sans attendre.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002230_RANJIT<tab>You are in no position to make demands.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002230_RANJIT<tab>Pas tant que vous n'aurez pas rempli quelques conditions. Écoutez-moi sagement.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002240_RANJIT<tab>By Lord Vauthry's decree, Rak'tika now falls under the governance of Eulmore. You will henceforth answer to us.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002240_RANJIT<tab>Cette forêt est désormais sous le contrôle d'Eulmore, sur ordre de notre maître don Vauthry. À partir de cet instant, vous devez nous obéir.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002250_YSHTOLA<tab>Is that so...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002250_YSHTOLA<tab>Que de propos déraisonnables...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002251_YSHTOLA<tab>And the Children of the Everlasting Dark have acquiesced to this madness?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002251_YSHTOLA<tab>Mais vu votre compagnie, la pilule a l'air d'être passée du côté des enfants des Ténèbres éternelles<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002260_RANJIT<tab>We have reached an accord, yes.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002260_RANJIT<tab>Ces personnes ont eu l'in<var 16 /var>tel<var 16 /var>li<var 16 /var>gence de conclure un accord avec notre maître avant que tout ceci n'arrive.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002270_RANJIT<tab>Too many times have the Night's Blessed shunned Eulmore's overtures of friendship. The risk that you harbor hostile intentions has grown too great to ignore.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002270_RANJIT<tab>Con<var 16 /var>trai<var 16 /var>re<var 16 /var>ment à vous, qui avez à maintes reprises refusé le protectorat eulmorien. Votre communauté incarne la menace même d'une rébellion.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002280_RANJIT<tab>Therefore his lordship has claimed dominion over this forest, and bestowed executive authority upon the Children of the Everlasting Dark.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002280_RANJIT<tab>C'est ainsi que mon maître a fait des Enfants ses alliés, et leur a accordé la souveraineté de ces lieux.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002290_EVERLASTINGDARKNESS<tab>In his wisdom, Lord Vauthry has agreed to recognize ours as the only permissible expression of Dark worship─its one true faith.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002290_EVERLASTINGDARKNESS<tab>Don Vauthry nous l'a promis<var 1D /var>: quand la région sera sous domination eulmorienne, seuls les enfants des Ténèbres éternelles seront légitimement reconnus.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002300_EVERLASTINGDARKNESS<tab>You and your false creed are a blight on these woods! A foul, unholy corruption that must be cleansed.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002300_EVERLASTINGDARKNESS<tab>À ce qu'on raconte, <var 08 E905 ((la Guerrière)) ((le Guerrier)) /var> des Ténèbres a honoré Grand-Lac et Il Mheg de sa présence<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002310_EVERLASTINGDARKNESS<tab>Little wonder the Warrior of Darkness visits both Lakeland and Il Mheg, yet shuns Rak'tika. Your perverted teachings hold blessed shadow at bay!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002310_EVERLASTINGDARKNESS<tab>Vous voulez savoir pourquoi <var 08 E905 ((elle)) ((il)) /var> n'est pas venu<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> nous voir en premier<var 1D /var>? C'est parce que votre culte mollasson et sans intérêt semble être le principal dans la région<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002320_YSHTOLA<tab>You have accepted the yoke of Eulmore to spite us, then? Fools. Darkness will never return to these skies while they hold sway.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002320_YSHTOLA<tab>C'est votre haine envers nous qui vous a poussés à vous tourner vers Eulmore... Mais ce partenariat ne vous apportera pas les Ténèbres. Bien au contraire<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002330_RANJIT<tab>Those of you minded to obey his lordship are to make for Woven Oath with all haste. We will leave you, that you may have time to prepare.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002330_RANJIT<tab>Je vous accorde un peu de répit. Que les membres du peuple de la Nuit désireux de s'incliner devant Eulmore nous rejoignent à Solide Serment.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002340_RUNAR<tab>Woven Oath!? Are you suggesting we abandon our faith to join those zealots!?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002340_RUNAR<tab>Au hameau des enfants des Ténèbres éternelles<var 1D /var>!? Pourquoi devrions-nous tirer un trait sur nos convictions et trahir nos prières<var 1D /var>!?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002350_EVERLASTINGDARKNESS<tab>What has your “faith” afforded you thus far? Nothing! <var 1A 02 /var>We<var 1A 01 /var> will guide you along the righteous path.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002350_EVERLASTINGDARKNESS<tab>Vos prières, personne ne les entend<var 1D /var>! Mais ne vous inquiétez pas, on va vous apprendre comment faire<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002360_YSHTOLA<tab>And should we refuse?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002360_YSHTOLA<tab>Et pour ceux qui resteront ici<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002370_RANJIT<tab>Anyone found here upon our return will be considered a traitor to Eulmore, and dealt with as such.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002370_RANJIT<tab>Je pensais que c'était clair... Cela sera considéré comme un acte de rébellion méritant châtiment.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002380_YSHTOLA<tab>We will discuss these developments after I have tended to our casualty.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002380_YSHTOLA<tab>Rentrons pour parler de tout ça... Je vous rejoins dès que je me serai occupée de lui.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002390_YSHTOLA<tab>'Twould seem we have found them.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002390_YSHTOLA<tab>... Le comité d'accueil<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002400_ALMET<tab>(-Bow-wielding Sentinel-)You trespass upon sacred ground. Begone!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002400_ALMET<tab>(-Gardienne à l'arc-)Personne n'a le droit de fouler ces terres, envahisseurs<var 1D /var>! Retournez d'où vous venez<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002410_YSHTOLA<tab>Wait! We did not come to─
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002410_YSHTOLA<tab>Non, attendez<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002420_UIMET<tab>(ATTACK GRUNT)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002420_UIMET<tab>Yaaa<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002430_YSHTOLA<tab>(BLOCKING GRUNT)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002430_YSHTOLA<tab>Hu<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002440_YSHTOLA<tab>Stop! We mean you no harm!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002440_YSHTOLA<tab>Je vous ai demandé d'attendre, non<var 1D /var>!?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002450_CYMET<tab>(-Staff-wielding Sentinel-)Sister. Is that─?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002450_CYMET<tab>(-Gardienne au sceptre-)T'as vu, Almet<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002460_YSHTOLA<tab>We are allies of the empire of Ronka. As is customary, we come bearing the seal of the emperor.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002460_YSHTOLA<tab>On l'a obtenu... en suivant les indications... de l'empire de Ronka. Nous sommes des alliés.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002470_UIMET<tab>Hmmm...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002470_UIMET<tab>Hum<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002480_UIMET<tab>(GASP)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002480_UIMET<tab>Aaah<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002490_UIMET<tab>(-Spear-wielding Sentinel-)It appears to be genuine!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002490_UIMET<tab>(-Gardienne à la lance-)On dirait un vrai<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002500_CYMET<tab>(-Staff-wielding Sentinel-)Then perhaps there is yet hope!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002500_CYMET<tab>(-Gardienne au sceptre-)Ça veut dire que tout n'est pas perdu<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002510_ALMET<tab>(-Bow-wielding Sentinel-)Perhaps...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002510_ALMET<tab>(-Gardienne à l'arc-)Ça m'en a tout l'air...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002520_ALMET<tab>(-Bow-wielding Sentinel-)We acknowledge your seal, but we must be certain of its authenticity.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002520_ALMET<tab>(-Gardienne à l'arc-)Vous brandissez le sceau de Ronka, mais nous devons nous assurer de son authenticité.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002530_ALMET<tab>(-Bow-wielding Sentinel-)Follow the azure flowers to our village. There we will judge if you are friend or foe.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002530_ALMET<tab>(-Gardienne à l'arc-)Nous vous attendrons dans notre hameau. Les fleurs bleues vous y guideront.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002540_UIMET<tab>(-Spear-wielding Sentinel-)Try not to stray from the path, all right?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002540_UIMET<tab>(-Gardienne à la lance-)Vous perdez pas en route, hein<var 1D /var>? À bientôt<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002550_YSHTOLA<tab>"Follow the flowers...“ Would it kill them to escort us?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002550_YSHTOLA<tab>(soupire)... Je rêve d'un monde où nos interlocuteurs prendraient le temps d'écouter avant d'attaquer...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002560_YSHTOLA<tab>But if it affords us an opportunity to investigate Yx'Maja...fine.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002560_YSHTOLA<tab>Enfin, on va pouvoir négocier. C'est le plus important... Montrons-nous coopératifs<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002570_YSHTOLA<tab>It seems to be working!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002570_YSHTOLA<tab>C'est bon<var 1D /var>! Ça a marché<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002580_ALMET<tab>(TAKING HIT REAX)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002580_ALMET<tab>Gouah<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002590_UIMET<tab>(TAKING HIT REAX)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002590_UIMET<tab>Ouah<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002600_CYMET<tab>(TAKING HIT REAX)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002600_CYMET<tab>Aaah<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002610_YSHTOLA<tab>I think not!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002610_YSHTOLA<tab>Pas si vite<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002620_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>General! Hold on!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002620_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>Laissez-moi vous aider<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002630_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>Hm?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002630_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>Hum...<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002640_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>(SCREAM)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002640_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>Ho...<var 1D /var>!?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002650_YSHTOLA<tab>Expertly done.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002650_YSHTOLA<tab>Quelle andouille... Tu as déclenché un piège<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002660_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>How was I to know that that would happen!? It looked like any other part of the floor!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002660_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>J-j'ai pas fait exprès<var 1D /var>! Je... Je pouvais pas savoir<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002670_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>...Might now be an opportune time to strike a bargain?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002670_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>Dites<var 1D /var>! Euh... Et si on faisait un marché<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002680_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>We poisoned a number of villagers in Slitherbough with a toxin brewed for us by the Children.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002680_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>Quand on a pris le contrôle de Serpentige, on a empoisonné les rebelles à l'aide d'une puissante toxine, fabriquée par les enfants des Ténèbres éternelles.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002690_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>This is the antidote.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002690_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>Et ça, c'est l'antidote...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05002_002700_EULMOREADJUTANT<tab>I daresay you know how potent their concoctions are─and the futility of trying to counteract their effects.
